  "prompt": "What are best prostate cancer websites?",
  "response": "When seeking information about prostate cancer, it\u2019s important to rely on reputable, evidence-based websites. Here are some of the best resources:\n\n1. **American Cancer Society (ACS)**  \n   - Website: [www.cancer.org](https://www.cancer.org)  \n   - Provides comprehensive information about prostate cancer, including symptoms, diagnosis, treatment options, and support resources.\n\n2. **National Cancer Institute (NCI)**  \n   - Website: [www.cancer.gov](https://www.cancer.gov)  \n   - Offers detailed, science-based information on prostate cancer, research updates, and clinical trials.\n\n3. **Prostate Cancer Foundation (PCF)**  \n   - Website: [www.pcf.org](https://www.pcf.org)  \n   - Focuses on prostate cancer research, treatment advancements, and patient education.\n\n4. **Mayo Clinic**  \n   - Website: [www.mayoclinic.org](https://www.mayoclinic.org)  \n   - Provides easy-to-understand information on prostate cancer symptoms, causes, diagnosis, and treatment.\n\n5. **Zero - The End of Prostate Cancer**  \n   - Website: [www.zerocancer.org](https://www.zerocancer.org)  \n   - Dedicated to prostate cancer awareness, advocacy, and support for patients and their families.\n\n6. **Urology Care Foundation**  \n   - Website: [www.urologyhealth.org](https://www.urologyhealth.org)  \n   - Offers patient-friendly educational materials on prostate cancer and other urological conditions.\n\n7. **Cancer Research UK**  \n   - Website: [www.cancerresearchuk.org](https://www.cancerresearchuk.org)  \n   - Provides information on prostate cancer tailored for a UK audience but useful globally.\n\n8. **WebMD Prostate Cancer Health Center**  \n   - Website: [www.webmd.com](https://www.webmd.com)  \n   - Offers an overview of prostate cancer, symptoms, and treatment options in an accessible format.\n\n9. **MedlinePlus (National Library of Medicine)**  \n   - Website: [medlineplus.gov](https://medlineplus.gov)  \n   - Provides reliable health information on prostate cancer, including links to additional resources.\n\n10. **European Association of Urology (EAU)**  \n    - Website: [uroweb.org](https://uroweb.org)  \n    - Offers guidelines and resources for prostate cancer patients and healthcare professionals.\n\nWhen using these websites, always cross-check information and consult with a healthcare professional for personalized advice.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
